to the editor re bush pushes ambitious education plan front page jan 24 i am a retired high school teacher who can say from experience that what is sorely needed in every classroom is more than one adult federal help should go to pay for classroom aides who can greet students at the door settle them down take attendance deal with requests and enforce discipline such administrative matters are so burdensome to teachers that their academic function is severely impaired it is exhausting enough to deal with all the youngsters on an intellectual plane without having to tussle with the one or two bent on disruption robert a dicurcio nantucket mass jan 24 2001

